BodyName: Committee on Rules, Privileges and Elections

Items.Title:
Oversight: Public Hearing on appointments to the New York City Board of Elections being considered by the Democratic members of the New York City Council pursuant to the New York State Election Law.

Bianka Perez is being considered for appointment by the Democratic members of the New York City Council as the Bronx County Democrat to the New York City Board of Elections to serve for the remainder of a four-year term that expires on December 31, 2016. 
 
Alan Schulkin is being considered for appointment by the Democratic members of the New York City Council as the New York County Democrat to the New York City Board of Elections to serve for the remainder of a four-year term that expires on December 31, 2016. 
 
John Flateau, Ph.D., is being considered for appointment by the Democratic members of the New York City Council as the Kings County Democrat to the New York City Board of Elections to serve for the remainder of a four-year term that expires on December 31, 2016.
Items.ActionText: This Oversight was Hearing Held by Committee
Items.MatterName: Oversight: Public Hearing on appointments to the New York City Board of Elections being considered by the Democratic members of the New York City Council pursuant to the New York State Election Law.
